harlow.utils.test_functions.lldeh_1d(x: numpy.ndarray, a: float) → numpy.ndarray[source]#

An interesting 1D non-linear function.

Source: https://www.reddit.com/r/math/comments/5mwr9g/what_are_your_favourite_or_most_interesting/ # noqa E301 :param x: :param a: parameter to control the shape, interesting variants: a=0, a=2.1

Returns:

harlow.utils.test_functions.ackley_nd(x_mx: numpy.ndarray, a: float = 20.0, b: float = 0.2, c: float = 2 * np.pi) → numpy.ndarray[source]#

n-dimensional Ackley function based on https://www.sfu.ca/~ssurjano/ackley.html.

Parameters

  • x_mx – Independent variable values, [x1, x2, …, xd], vectorized input is supported (provide them along the row dimension).

  • a – Constant/parameter in the function.

  • b – Constant/parameter in the function.

  • c – Constant/parameter in the function.

Returns

Dependent variable values.
